Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Drawable
    Interface for all Drawable objects Contains abstract methods, which are needed for the DrawableList
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Node
    The Class for the Node object Implements the Drawable interface, since it is a drawable object The node object displays to the user their inputted early and late event times It also links Tasks together Each node has a unique index and HashSets of preceding and succeeding tasks
    TaskVisualised
    Class for the TaskVisualised object Implements the Drawable interface, since it is a drawable object Each TaskVisualised represents a task, and is painted into the PathComponent Painted as a line with a number to represent its duration, and an arrow to show its direction (In comments, 'the Task' refers to the Task which this object represents)
